						<summary>

						<p>This inscription refers to the gift of land for worship and carry out repair work in the temple <hi rend="italic">Nayinār Tirumurugī</hi> [śvaramu]ḍaiya-Tambiraṉār at Rājakēśvari [nallūr] <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Taiyūr in [Ā]yiravēlippaṟṟu a village of Kumiḻi nāḍu, which was a sub-division of Āmūr kōṭṭam. It is stated that the land was situated in Kuṉranallūr in Iraṇḍāyiravēlippaṟṟu, which was the hamlet of Saundariyachōḻapuram in Puḻar kōṭṭam a sub-division of [Jayaṅgo]ṇḍachōḻa maṇḍalam.</p>						

						</summary>
